<HEADLINE>
<P>
BAN ON BARBECUE LIGHTER FLUID 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The South Coast Air Quality Management District (Part A, Oct. 6) has acted to 
cleanse the basin of the scourge of barbecue lighter fluid. 
</P>
<P>
This bold, damn-the-torpedoes move, we are told, will reduce our daily dose of 
air poison by two tons. 
</P>
<P>
With one of the new, cleaner-burning gasolines trimming 15 tons from the 6,300 
tons said to come from cars each day, we shall soon be back to blue skies 
again. 
</P>
<P>
Any chance these guys are kidding? 
</P>
<P>
VICTOR BOESEN, Pacific Palisades 
</P>
</TEXT>
