<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: ARTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Free-Market Bolshoi: A touring ballet company that will exist on ticket sales 
alone has been formed, announced artistic director Yuri Grigorovich in New York 
on Thursday. The 60-member group, named Bolshoi Ballet Grigorovich Company, 
will be independent of any government funding and will be made up of young 
dancers graduating from the leading ballet academies in the Soviet Union. It 
makes its debut appearance at Texas A&amp;M University on Nov. 23, with 
Grigorovich's "Nutcracker," followed by a five-city tour. BETH KLEID 
</P>
