MORNING REPORT: MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Unchained Movie: The hit movie "Ghost" is scaring people into theaters abroad. 
The film grossed $2,854,732 on 233 screens during its first three days in 
release in the United Kingdom and Ireland last weekend, achieving the biggest 
three-day gross of any film released in the United Kingdom this year. In Japan, 
the film's second weekend gross at 11 theaters brought a gross of $2,169,316 
for a 10-day per-screen average of $197,211, it was announced by Barry London, 
president of the Paramount Pictures' Motion Picture Group. BETH KLEID 
