<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTHEAD'S NUGGETS LOSE BIG IN DEBUT, 186-123 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TEMPE, Ariz. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Denver Nugget Coach Paul Westhead's run-and gun style that he used at Loyola 
Marymount backfired as the Phoenix Suns routed the Nuggets, 186-123, in the NBA 
exhibition opener for both teams Thursday night. 
</P>
<P>
Phoenix rookie forward Cedric Ceballos, who made all 12 of his field-goal 
attempts, scored 29 points and Eddie Johnson added 27 for the Suns. 
</P>
<P>
Ceballos, a second-round draft pick out of Cal State Fullerton, scored 18 
points in the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
It was the most points the Suns have scored in any game in their 23-year 
history. Their regular-season team record is 160, set against Portland on March 
21, 1972. 
</P>
<P>
The Suns, whose regular-season team record for points in one half is 91 set 
Nov. 1, 1984 against Portland, led 89-64 at halftime despite missing 22 of 
their 50 field-goal attempts. 
</P>
<P>
Denver committed 48 personal fouls, and Phoenix made 52 of 71 free-throw 
attempts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
