<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
ROYAL EXTENDS LEAGUE STREAK TO 45 VICTORIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Royal High extended its Marmonte League water polo winning streak to 45 matches 
and repelled Thousand Oaks' bid for the league lead with a 12-3 win Thursday at 
Rancho Simi Pool in Simi Valley. 
</P>
<P>
In a battle of league co-leaders, Royal, ranked seventh in the Southern Section 
3-A Division, shut Thousand Oaks down with a pressing defense and strong play 
from goalies Ralph Radka and Paul Krueger, who combined for 15 saves. 
</P>
<P>
Five players scored two goals each for Royal (13-3, 4-0). 
</P>
<P>
Thousand Oaks is 8-7, 3-1. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
GIRLS' VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
Thousand Oaks d. Agoura, 15-3, 15-7, 15-1 -- Visiting Thousand Oaks, ranked 
fifth in the Southern Section 5-A Division, pounced on Agoura (4-4 in Marmonte 
League play). Aimee Stone had 10 kills and Jennifer Streltzoff six kills and 20 
assists for Thousand Oaks (11-1, 8-0). 
</P>
<P>
Royal d. Newbury Park, 15-12, 15-7, 7-15, 9-15, 15-10 -- Wende Brown had 31 
kills, a single-match school record, to lead Royal in a Marmonte League match 
at Newbury Park. Jennifer Hamilton added 15 kills for Royal (9-1, 7-1). 
</P>
<P>
Notre Dame d. Alemany, 15-5, 15-6, 15-3 -- Mary Strong had 11 kills and Jill 
Howden had 11 service points to lead host Notre Dame in a Mission League match. 
</P>
<P>
Notre Dame (8-2, 4-0) has won eight consecutive matches and is ranked second in 
the Southern Section 4-A Division. 
</P>
<P>
Burroughs d. Schurr, 15-6, 11-15, 15-6, 15-1 -- Jennifer Wagner had 27 kills 
and Carmen Gutierrez added 10 for Burroughs (11-1, 4-0) in a Foothill League 
match at home. 
</P>
<P>
Taft d. Reseda, 15-6, 15-2, 14-16, 15-9 -- Sarah White, with 14 kills, was the 
main beneficiary of setter Dara Kaskinen, who had 24 assists for Taft (6-1, 
3-1) in a Northwest Valley Conference match at Taft. 
</P>
<P>
El Camino Real d. Cleveland, 15-3, 15-5, 15-5 -- Jennifer Dinaberg had 13 kills 
for host El Camino Real (6-0, 3-0) in a Northwest Valley Conference match. 
</P>
<P>
Chatsworth d. Kennedy, 15-3, 15- 13, 15-0 -- Heather Gorman and Jody Paperno 
each had seven kills for Chatsworth (7-0, 3-0) in a Northwest Valley Conference 
match at home. 
</P>
<P>
Village Christian d. Montclair Prep, 15-3, 15-4, 15-5 -- Jennifer Kossuth had 
19 kills for host Village Christian (7-1, 4-0 in Alpha League play). 
</P>
<P>
Moorpark d. Bishop Diego, 15-5, 15-10, 15-6 -- Kristie Evans led Moorpark (8-0, 
4-0) with nine kills in a Tri-Valley League match at Moorpark. 
</P>
