<TEXT>
<P>
A North Park woman was seriously injured when she was struck by a car Thursday 
in Hillcrest, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Denise Louise Wix, 36, of the 3700 block of Grim Avenue was struck by a car 
driven by a 16-year-old San Diego High School student who failed to stop as Wix 
and a friend were crossing Pershing Drive near University Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
Wix was listed in critical condition at Mercy Hospital with head injuries and 
cuts. Her companion, Bibana Garces Cabanging, 55, of the 1300 block of Twining 
