<P>
Proceedings began Thursday to revoke the license of the largest-grossing bingo 
parlor in Los Angeles, with city officials releasing affidavits by four 
ex-workers of the Woodland Hills operation alleging they were illegally paid up 
to $300 a night from skimmed cash. 
</P>
<P>
