<P>
LOTTO PLAYER WINS $50-MILLION JACKPOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A warehouse manager from Erie, Pa., won Ohio's record $50-million Super Lotto 
jackpot, the second largest lottery payoff to a single winner in the United 
States. Richard Hovis, 37, took a limousine to Ohio Lottery Commission 
headquarters in Cleveland to surrender his ticket. It was the 12th largest 
jackpot nationally, but his total take was second only to the $55.2 million won 
by a Florida woman. 
</P>
