NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Quarterback Bobby Hebert, now residing in Manhattan Beach, is suing the Raiders 
for not signing him. 
</P>
<P>
Hebert, unable to reach a contract agreement with the New Orleans Saints this 
season, claims in a suit filed in Los Angeles that the Raiders, in observing 
the NFL's Plan B system for transferring players, are violating California law 
by preventing a person from pursuing his livelihood. 
</P>
<P>
The complaint claims that the Raiders "have actively tried to make a trade for 
Hebert, but have been prevented from doing so by the demand of New Orleans for 
enormous compensation." 
