<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL REPORT / WEEKDAY UPDATE; 
</P>
<P>
UCLA; 
</P>
<P>
BRUINS PASS WELL, DEFEND PASS WELL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAL FLORENCE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UCLA has the distinction of leading the Pacific 10 Conference in passing 
offense and pass-efficiency defense with a 94.3 rating. 
</P>
<P>
The Bruins are averaging 265.8 yards a game passing, while allowing an average 
of 148.4 through five games. 
</P>
<P>
Moreover, only two touchdown passes have been thrown against the Bruins. MAL 
FLORENCE 
</P>
</TEXT>
